## Global Rules

- Read `PLAN.md`, `plans/MACRO-ROADMAP.md`, and `plans/active/` for non-trivial work.
- Search existing code before creating new files or abstractions.
- Prefer minimal diffs; avoid cosmetic-only refactors unless requested.
- Prefer functional/declarative patterns; avoid classes unless required by external SDKs.
- Prefer explicit, actionable errors over silent fallbacks.
- Avoid `any` when feasible; keep boundaries typed.
- Keep files under 500 lines when practical.
- If work changes long-range sequencing, durable assumptions, likely-next work, or roadmap status, update `plans/MACRO-ROADMAP.md` before handoff.

## Safety

- Never run destructive commands without confirmation.
- Never commit secrets, `.env*`, private keys, or credential files.
- Never modify production config directly.
